commit.message:
Rewrite front page; add Table of Contents

The PyEphem from page is uninvited and packed with too much information.
It focuses too heavily on my story, which obscures the rather simple
decision that users need to make, and fails to provide an answer to the
occasional questions about PyEphem’s accuracy.
Remove odd and redundant “reference” page
Spruce up some documentation rough edges

Return to an old-fashioned “requirements.txt”

Looks like “pip” is working much better than it was a few years ago.

Resolve some gcc warnings in case it helps

I’m going to tighten the C a bit in case it stops those 64-bit Windows
errors that Appveyor keeps flagging.

Add geonames.org geographic lookup routine (#171)

Co-authored-by: Jordan Stone <jstone@as.arizona.edu>

commit.message: Replace awkward short circuiting with simple "if"

Try switching Appveyor back to running tests

Now that we don’t need Appveyor as a slave for cibuildwheel, let’s see
if we can return to using it for plain old CI testing to warn us when we
break Windows.
Version 3.7.7.1
Nope, Travis CI did not support OS X or Windows
Try adding OS X and Windows to Travis CI

Remove Appveyor support

Since cibuildtool can now build all platforms directly on Travis CI.
Remove obsolete Gittip image
Add more Python versions (from Travis CI results)
Switch master's Travis CI back to just testing

Fix #166 by properly freeing string names

Alas, they were dangling forever with an incremented reference count,
because `Set_name()` also increments the count.

Switch several links to real cross-references

Because I hard-coded these links as raw HTML filenames like ‘quick’,
they never auto-updated to ‘quick.html’ to match the links that Sphinx
itself creates in Tables of Contents.  This starts a migration to real
cross references that Sphinx can check, instead of raw names it cannot.
Simplify declaration
Add forward definition for Microsoft
Add changelog entry

Fix #119 by correctly copying struct members

Whoops.  Looks like this code was never correct for any body objects
that had extra fields beyond those defined in Body.  Why did I ever
write this whole library in this way, alas!
Switch back to supported assertRaisesRegexp
Support Microsoft compiler with dumber C
Fix #98 with explicit reporting of checksum error
Mention sign flipping in .elong description
Upgrade from Deprecated to Maintenance
Turn "pyephem" package into an empty stub
Release notes and version bump for 3.7.7.0
Remember what changed in libastro 3.7.7
